2.6.1 Supply description

Description: The element <supplyDescr> contains the information on each item 
of supply or set of supplies.

The attribute id in the element <supplyDescr> can be applied so that the supply 
can be cross-referenced from the procedure.

  
Markup element: <supplyDescr>

Attributes:
The element <supplyDescr> contains the same attributes as the element 
<supportEquipDescr> (refer to Para 2.5.1 ) with the addition of the configurable attributes:
- supplyCategory (O), the category of supply (identifies if a supply is, for example 
a consumable, material or expendable). The attribute can have one of the following values:
  • "supcat01" thru "supcat99". Refer to Chap 3.9.6.1 and with the different use for attribute:
- materialUsage (O), identifies retained and referenced supplies. It also identifies 
a material set of supplies. The attribute can have one of the following values:
  • "mu01" thru "mu99". Refer to Chap 3.9.6.1 and default BREX rule BREX-S1-00074.
  Use of the attribute materialUsage:
  • For supplies needed from store and required to do the task, the attribute 
  materialUsage is not used. It is used only for supplies removed from 
  the Product or for supplies when used to define a material set 
  (attribute materialUsage = "mu05"). Refer to Chap 3.9.6.1.
  • For supplies, the values "Discarded"(attribute materialUsage = "mu01") 
  and "Modified from" (attribute materialUsage="mu03") must not be used.
  • For supplies, the value "Retained" (attribute materialUsage = "mu02") 
  must be used only in the context of a service bulletin.

Child elements:
The element <supplyDescr> contains the same elements as the element 
<supportEquipDescr> (refer to Para 2.5.1 ) with the following exceptions:
- <toolRef> is substituted with the elements <supplyRef> and the element 
<supplyRqmtRef>. Refer to Para 2.6.1.1 for details on the element <supplyRef>.
Refer to Para 2.6.1.2 for details on the element <supplyRqmtRef>.
- <hazards> is added as a child of <supplyDescr>. Refer to Chap 3.9.5.2.11.7.
- <embeddedSupportEquipDescr> is substituted with the element 
<embeddedSupplyDescr>. Refer toPara 2.6.1.3.

Business rule decision point BRDP-S1-00155 - Use of the attribute id on the element 
<supplyDescr> in the element <preliminaryRqmts>:
– Decide whether to use the attribute id to create cross-references from the procedure 
to the supplies listed in Preliminary requirements. The attribute id on the element 
<supplyDescr> is used to establish the link between the two and will guarantee
consistent use of identification throughout the procedure. 
The use of cross-references is encouraged.

  
